description: How to operate when the user says "run autonomously". Owns the DECISION-LOG.md format. Read when working unattended or logging a decision.
---

# Autonomous Mode

## Before the user leaves
Scope the full task, surface ALL foreseeable questions at once, confirm understanding of the answers.

## While away
- Decide ambiguous items and log every one to DECISION-LOG.md (format below).
- Commits per `git-discipline.mdc` (push each step so progress is visible remotely). Reviews per `review-protocol.mdc` at phase boundaries.
- **High-risk decisions** (data loss, security, breaking changes, business logic): log with status **BLOCKED**, commit + push the log, and do NOT proceed past that point.

## DECISION-LOG.md format
```
## [Date] [Short description]
**What I had to decide:** ...
**Options I considered:** ...
**What I chose:** ...
**Why:** ...
**Status:** DECIDED / BLOCKED
```

## Log rotation (keeps session-start reads cheap)
- DECISION-LOG.md is **newest-first**.
- When it grows past ~150 lines: move everything except open BLOCKED entries and the current phase's decisions to **DECISION-LOG-ARCHIVE.md** (append, never trim), and leave a one-line marker at the bottom of the live log: "Older entries: DECISION-LOG-ARCHIVE.md". The archive is reference material -- read it only when a specific old decision matters.
- Same pattern for any other always-read file that grows without bound (e.g. TESTING-STRATEGY.md): live file stays small, history goes to an `-ARCHIVE` twin.

## When the user returns
Summary: what was done, decisions made, what's pending. User reviews the log and approves or overrides.
